281
00:21:03,705 --> 00:21:05,545
If you do a job you enjoy,

282
00:21:06,504 --> 00:21:08,105
at least, you will be happy.

283
00:21:08,185 --> 00:21:09,625
Then you will do that job well.

284
00:21:15,504 --> 00:21:16,665
Mom.

285
00:21:16,744 --> 00:21:18,705
-What is it?
-What?

286
00:21:18,784 --> 00:21:20,545
-What's going on?
-I'm touched.

287
00:21:21,105 --> 00:21:21,945
-Touched?
-Gen.

288
00:21:22,024 --> 00:21:24,465
I thought you wanted to wipe your mouth.

289
00:21:25,024 --> 00:21:26,465
-Here.
-Come on.

290
00:21:27,264 --> 00:21:28,984
Our little puppy.

291
00:21:29,065 --> 00:21:30,185
Puppies come from dogs.

292
00:21:30,264 --> 00:21:32,665
-That backfired.
-Look at him.

293
00:21:32,744 --> 00:21:34,225
You're never like this.

294
00:21:34,305 --> 00:21:36,504
-Come on.
-Okay, you're touched.

295
00:21:36,585 --> 00:21:38,585
I love you too.

296
00:21:38,665 --> 00:21:40,264
-Can I hug you?
-Come here.

297
00:21:41,825 --> 00:21:42,905
You little puppy.

298
00:21:44,225 --> 00:21:45,984
Had Nut had a warm

299
00:21:46,465 --> 00:21:48,105
and understanding family,

300
00:21:50,065 --> 00:21:53,945
he would've grown up to be
a happy young man like Gen.

301
00:22:00,024 --> 00:22:03,385
THE LITTLE PRINCE

302
00:22:06,984 --> 00:22:08,345
You're home.

303
00:22:11,905 --> 00:22:12,984
What's wrong?

304
00:22:14,145 --> 00:22:15,544
Can you tell me?

305
00:23:48,825 --> 00:23:52,705
SONG: SLEEPING ALONE
MUST BE LONELY, MISTER

306
00:23:56,905 --> 00:23:59,225
I'M NOT LONELY

307
00:24:03,264 --> 00:24:05,105
I HAVE SOMEONE TO SLEEP WITH

308
00:24:18,065 --> 00:24:18,945
Gen.

309
00:24:19,425 --> 00:24:20,705
What?

310
00:24:21,665 --> 00:24:23,264
Will I get to live with Nut again?

311
00:24:27,185 --> 00:24:28,305
I don't know.

312
00:24:29,305 --> 00:24:31,185
You and Nut are the only ones who know.

313
00:24:33,544 --> 00:24:34,865
It's up to your hearts

314
00:24:35,425 --> 00:24:36,984
if you want to get back together.

315
00:24:39,145 --> 00:24:40,865
I really want to.

316
00:24:44,105 --> 00:24:45,105
But…

317
00:24:47,425 --> 00:24:48,465
Nut…

318
00:24:50,105 --> 00:24:51,744
Stop sulking.

319
00:24:54,065 --> 00:24:55,385
Nut is just confused.

320
00:24:56,024 --> 00:24:58,264
It's hard for him to move on

321
00:24:59,024 --> 00:25:00,625
and start over, you know?

322
00:25:03,905 --> 00:25:06,665
He probably had high hopes,

323
00:25:07,585 --> 00:25:10,065
and you must have disappointed him.

324
00:25:10,945 --> 00:25:12,304
Give him time.

325
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:14,544
I'll talk to him.

326
00:25:32,225 --> 00:25:35,585
SONG: WHO? WHO ARE YOU SLEEPING WITH?

327
00:25:35,665 --> 00:25:38,865
ARE YOU CHEATING ON ME?

328
00:25:38,945 --> 00:25:44,984
MISTER, DON'T

329
00:25:46,065 --> 00:25:47,145
Nut.

330
00:25:48,425 --> 00:25:50,585
I want to be back by your side.

331
00:25:52,304 --> 00:25:54,185
I will not give up.

332
00:26:02,385 --> 00:26:04,385
BE WITH YOU

333
00:26:06,145 --> 00:26:06,984
Wait.

334
00:26:08,145 --> 00:26:09,264
You're not Neung.

335
00:26:09,945 --> 00:26:11,744
Isn't he your friend?

336
00:26:12,544 --> 00:26:15,784
He fell from your balcony
yesterday morning.

337
00:26:34,145 --> 00:26:35,865
Who gave you that pork recipe?

338
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:38,105
I just followed my gut.

339
00:26:49,705 --> 00:26:51,625
I'm your teddy bear.

340
00:28:33,825 --> 00:28:35,825
I'm your teddy bear.

341
00:28:38,425 --> 00:28:39,264
But…

342
00:28:40,225 --> 00:28:41,585
I have no idea

343
00:28:42,345 --> 00:28:44,304
how I turned into a human.

344
00:28:45,504 --> 00:28:48,544
Do you really think Tofu is a teddy bear?

345
00:28:49,465 --> 00:28:50,865
Who would be that crazy?

346
00:28:52,625 --> 00:28:54,865
I just thought it might have
something to do with…

347
00:28:55,425 --> 00:28:57,024
Is this about your ex again?

348
00:28:59,625 --> 00:29:02,225
Do you think your ex revolves around you

349
00:29:02,905 --> 00:29:04,705
like a planet orbiting around the sun?

350
00:29:07,145 --> 00:29:08,705
I'm not just imagining it.

351
00:29:09,425 --> 00:29:10,984
I have my reasons.

352
00:29:12,544 --> 00:29:15,264
Tofu reminds me of him all the time.

353
00:29:16,744 --> 00:29:20,105
Nut, there are tens of millions of people
in this country.

354
00:29:20,585 --> 00:29:23,064
Don't you think
some of them talk and think alike?

355
00:29:24,504 --> 00:29:26,905
Tofu could've watched the same movies,

356
00:29:27,385 --> 00:29:28,784
read the same books,

357
00:29:28,865 --> 00:29:31,585
and listened to the same songs as your ex.

358
00:29:32,225 --> 00:29:33,425
That's why he said that.

359
00:29:34,425 --> 00:29:36,185
But what he said was special.

360
00:29:36,825 --> 00:29:38,385
He used the exact same words.

361
00:29:39,345 --> 00:29:40,425
So what?

362
00:29:41,225 --> 00:29:43,984
Did you think he sent Tofu here
to steal your teddy bear,

363
00:29:44,544 --> 00:29:46,225
say those lines,

364
00:29:46,825 --> 00:29:48,665
and love you in his place?

365
00:29:53,825 --> 00:29:55,385
If you can't answer it,

366
00:29:56,024 --> 00:29:59,185
why bother thinking about
impossible questions like that?

367
00:29:59,865 --> 00:30:02,385
You should think about the question
that you can answer.

368
00:30:03,465 --> 00:30:05,825
Do you still want Tofu in your life?

369
00:30:38,865 --> 00:30:40,665
So it's you

370
00:30:41,425 --> 00:30:42,465
who was with him.

371
00:30:44,744 --> 00:30:47,304
Why do you need to borrow my laptop?

372
00:30:47,945 --> 00:30:48,865
To get Nut back.

373
00:31:15,264 --> 00:31:20,225
I'M NOT LONELY WITHOUT YOU

374
00:31:23,465 --> 00:31:24,784
Why did you go to my house?

375
00:31:28,264 --> 00:31:29,544
Where are you taking Tofu?

376
00:31:34,465 --> 00:31:35,304
Here.

377
00:31:39,304 --> 00:31:40,425
I guess that's love.

378
00:31:42,064 --> 00:31:43,585
Even though he kicked you out,

379
00:31:44,064 --> 00:31:45,385
you still look after his mom.

380
00:31:48,504 --> 00:31:49,824
I promised Nut

381
00:31:50,625 --> 00:31:52,225
that I would take care of her.

382
00:31:54,145 --> 00:31:55,744
Even if he's still mad at me,

383
00:31:56,705 --> 00:31:58,385
I need to keep my promise.

384
00:32:00,064 --> 00:32:00,945
True love.

385
00:32:04,304 --> 00:32:05,345
I'm going now.

386
00:32:05,425 --> 00:32:06,705
Okay.

387
00:32:16,744 --> 00:32:18,264
-Look, Tofu is here.
-Tofu.

388
00:32:18,744 --> 00:32:20,744
-Tofu is here.
-Tofu.

389
00:32:20,824 --> 00:32:22,225
What a relief.

390
00:32:22,304 --> 00:32:25,465
I was praying for your safety all night.

391
00:32:27,705 --> 00:32:30,625
What about Ms. Left Slipper?

392
00:32:44,865 --> 00:32:46,984
Why did you come back alone?

393
00:32:47,504 --> 00:32:51,504
Mr. Right Slipper,
where's your girlfriend?

394
00:32:53,705 --> 00:32:56,345
I lost Ms. Left Slipper.

395
00:32:58,185 --> 00:32:59,024
What?

396
00:32:59,585 --> 00:33:00,744
My goodness.

397
00:33:01,544 --> 00:33:03,625
Little One shouldn't have helped you.

398
00:33:03,705 --> 00:33:06,585
You always call others ignorant.

399
00:33:07,145 --> 00:33:09,824
Well, your girlfriend
can't ignore you now.

400
00:33:17,064 --> 00:33:18,784
I promise you, Mr. Right Slipper,

401
00:33:19,744 --> 00:33:21,585
I'll find Little One.

402
00:33:22,585 --> 00:33:24,824
I would never lose Mrs. Na's belongings.

403
00:33:35,064 --> 00:33:36,304
Where's Mrs. Na?

404
00:34:43,545 --> 00:34:44,384
Oh…

405
00:34:48,944 --> 00:34:50,145
Thank you.

406
00:34:52,424 --> 00:34:53,465
Let me help.

407
00:35:04,185 --> 00:35:06,505
It wouldn't be as pretty
had I done it myself.

408
00:35:06,985 --> 00:35:09,505
Thank you for helping me.

409
00:35:10,705 --> 00:35:11,904
You're welcome.

410
00:35:21,424 --> 00:35:23,265
This area still seems a bit bare.

411
00:35:24,105 --> 00:35:26,745
Shall we buy some more plants?

412
00:35:30,225 --> 00:35:31,505
Are you free this Saturday?

413
00:35:37,904 --> 00:35:38,985
Let's take a photo

414
00:35:40,424 --> 00:35:44,505
as a memento of the three of us
arranging the garden together.

415
00:35:50,545 --> 00:35:51,705
I'll put the chair away.

416
00:35:52,465 --> 00:35:53,384
Let me help.

417
00:36:50,505 --> 00:36:52,745
I need to research a lot
for the subject I teach,

418
00:36:53,505 --> 00:36:55,424
in order to explain it to the children.

419
00:36:58,825 --> 00:37:00,904
But the more I research,

420
00:37:01,384 --> 00:37:02,904
the more questions I have.

421
00:37:04,904 --> 00:37:06,464
Do you think

422
00:37:07,105 --> 00:37:09,625
Thai people really did migrate
from the Altai Mountains?

423
00:37:11,665 --> 00:37:13,424
And did the villagers of Bang Rachan

424
00:37:13,505 --> 00:37:17,585
really die fighting to protect Ayutthaya?

425
00:37:19,825 --> 00:37:20,904
So,

426
00:37:21,585 --> 00:37:23,265
is it not true?

427
00:37:26,625 --> 00:37:27,464
Well,

428
00:37:27,985 --> 00:37:29,825
I don't know much about this stuff.

429
00:37:30,745 --> 00:37:33,985
You might have to explain it to me
a bit more.

430
00:37:38,105 --> 00:37:39,545
Would you mind

431
00:37:40,145 --> 00:37:42,705
if I asked you to come
and explain it to me every day?

432
00:37:47,185 --> 00:37:48,825
Maybe Thais didn't migrate here

433
00:37:49,384 --> 00:37:50,985
but have always been in this area.

434
00:37:52,785 --> 00:37:56,745
As for Bang Rachan, they didn't fight
for anyone but themselves.

435
00:37:59,025 --> 00:38:00,384
Is that what you think?

436
00:38:02,065 --> 00:38:06,305
History isn't a record
of what actually happened.

437
00:38:07,464 --> 00:38:10,265
It's just distorted recollections

438
00:38:11,225 --> 00:38:14,864
that are retold in a way
that suits whoever is telling them.

439
00:38:15,665 --> 00:38:16,785
Do you agree?

440
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:21,065
I didn't think…

441
00:38:22,625 --> 00:38:24,585
you would be interested in history.

442
00:38:25,904 --> 00:38:27,225
I like to read.

443
00:38:28,065 --> 00:38:31,464
History, philosophy, and literature.

444
00:38:33,505 --> 00:38:34,585
This one

445
00:38:35,424 --> 00:38:36,985
is my favorite.

446
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:38,065
THE LITTLE PRINCE

447
00:38:38,145 --> 00:38:39,384
"The Little Prince."

448
00:38:41,825 --> 00:38:44,105
I really like
the illustrations in this book.

449
00:38:45,105 --> 00:38:46,825
But when I was at school,

450
00:38:47,825 --> 00:38:49,785
I didn't really understand it.

451
00:38:51,545 --> 00:38:52,545
They say,

452
00:38:52,625 --> 00:38:55,864
older people perceive
The Little Prince differently

453
00:38:55,944 --> 00:38:58,305
than children.

454
00:38:59,225 --> 00:39:01,665
You should read it again.

455
00:39:01,745 --> 00:39:04,705
You might understand
and perceive it differently this time.

456
00:39:07,185 --> 00:39:08,145
Okay.

457
00:39:20,745 --> 00:39:22,185
Sib.

458
00:39:27,025 --> 00:39:28,105
Mrs. Na.

459
00:39:31,384 --> 00:39:32,944
When did you get here, Tofu?

460
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:36,025
Just now.

461
00:39:37,705 --> 00:39:39,825
Do you remember Mr. Sibmeun now?

462
00:39:45,785 --> 00:39:47,625
Do you want to tell me anything?

463
00:39:56,384 --> 00:39:57,705
-Thank you.
-It's okay.

464
00:40:07,105 --> 00:40:09,545
You all look happy in this picture.

465
00:40:10,785 --> 00:40:13,025
Why don't you want to think about it?

466
00:40:16,384 --> 00:40:18,384
Sometimes you are happy

467
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:22,265
at the start of a nightmare, Tofu.

468
00:40:26,585 --> 00:40:28,665
We can't have good dreams all the time.

469
00:40:31,705 --> 00:40:33,745
I have a secret to tell you.

470
00:40:33,825 --> 00:40:35,665
You're the first one to know.

471
00:40:43,305 --> 00:40:45,625
I've just started dreaming recently.

472
00:40:47,904 --> 00:40:49,424
Whenever I have a nightmare,

473
00:40:49,505 --> 00:40:51,625
I would really be glad when I wake up,

474
00:40:52,424 --> 00:40:54,424
because I know it's just a dream.

475
00:40:55,225 --> 00:40:56,185
It has passed.

476
00:40:56,745 --> 00:40:59,025
The monster in my dream
can't hurt me anymore.

477
00:41:00,424 --> 00:41:01,985
Whenever I have a good dream,

478
00:41:03,065 --> 00:41:05,105
I'm happy all day long.

479
00:41:08,944 --> 00:41:10,944
Don't you want

480
00:41:11,464 --> 00:41:13,185
to go back to sleep

481
00:41:14,105 --> 00:41:15,384
to continue the good dream?

482
00:41:17,065 --> 00:41:18,225
No.

483
00:41:19,225 --> 00:41:20,864
In my real life, I have Nut,

484
00:41:22,025 --> 00:41:23,345
you,

485
00:41:24,424 --> 00:41:26,065
and many other friends.

486
00:41:27,185 --> 00:41:29,265
Sometimes I'm happy. Sometimes I'm sad.

487
00:41:30,705 --> 00:41:32,384
But it's reality.

488
00:41:33,665 --> 00:41:35,625
I wouldn't trade it for a dream.

489
00:41:58,384 --> 00:41:59,464
Mrs. Na.

490
00:42:01,145 --> 00:42:02,944
Some nights you have good dreams.

491
00:42:04,105 --> 00:42:05,904
Some nights you have bad dreams.

492
00:42:07,985 --> 00:42:09,505
But in the end,

493
00:42:10,745 --> 00:42:12,825
you have to wake up.

494
00:42:45,545 --> 00:42:46,625
I've decided

495
00:42:47,105 --> 00:42:49,384
to borrow some money
from Sakon to help Na.

496
00:42:51,745 --> 00:42:53,384
Have you thought it through?

497
00:42:53,464 --> 00:42:54,705
She's struggling.

498
00:42:55,185 --> 00:42:58,105
She has to pay for her house
and her grandmother's medical bills.

499
00:42:58,185 --> 00:42:59,105
What can I do?

500
00:42:59,185 --> 00:43:00,625
It's pointless.

501
00:43:00,705 --> 00:43:02,665
You won't hold her grandmother back.

502
00:43:02,745 --> 00:43:05,185
It will just prolong her suffering.

503
00:43:05,745 --> 00:43:08,825
In the end,
the person who will suffer the most is Na.

504
00:43:10,384 --> 00:43:12,384
Is it Na or you who will suffer?

505
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:16,065
Do you think I don't know
what you're trying to do?

506
00:43:16,545 --> 00:43:20,424
Is it only a soldier with a bright future
like you who deserves Na?

507
00:43:20,505 --> 00:43:23,785
When we were kids, I may not have been
as good as you at anything,

508
00:43:24,545 --> 00:43:27,545
but I won't let you
walk all over me this time.

509
00:43:28,305 --> 00:43:30,025
You know Na loves me.

510
00:43:32,785 --> 00:43:34,705
I'm warning you with good intentions.

511
00:43:35,384 --> 00:43:38,785
Think it through.
The money will cause you trouble.

512
00:43:41,025 --> 00:43:42,345
I have thought it through.

513
00:43:43,065 --> 00:43:45,065
I will show both you and Na

514
00:43:45,545 --> 00:43:47,785
that I can make her happy too.

515
00:44:10,984 --> 00:44:12,745
May I give him a sponge bath?

516
00:44:12,825 --> 00:44:13,665
Go ahead.

517
00:45:49,745 --> 00:45:51,345
The lab results are in.

518
00:45:51,825 --> 00:45:54,384
We found a bloodstain
on the living room floor,

519
00:45:54,864 --> 00:45:56,424
but it had been cleaned.

520
00:45:56,505 --> 00:45:58,944
That means a fight occurred here.

521
00:45:59,904 --> 00:46:01,545
I think Tatarn

522
00:46:01,625 --> 00:46:04,464
could have been injured and moved.

523
00:46:05,505 --> 00:46:07,505
So, it seems like
he was attacked and killed.

524
00:46:07,585 --> 00:46:09,345
That means Saen lied to us.

525
00:46:12,145 --> 00:46:13,904
Should we issue a warrant?

526
00:46:15,145 --> 00:46:17,305
Not yet. Don't alert him.

527
00:46:18,345 --> 00:46:23,065
He went this far to deceive us.
He and his wife must have a solid plan.

528
00:46:24,305 --> 00:46:26,505
Find some solid evidence against him,

529
00:46:27,025 --> 00:46:28,464
then we'll arrest him.

530
00:46:40,225 --> 00:46:41,464
Lieutenant.

531
00:46:42,025 --> 00:46:43,505
Have a look around.

532
00:46:43,585 --> 00:46:45,225
There must be more evidence.

533
00:46:45,305 --> 00:46:46,464
Yes, sir.

534
00:46:55,705 --> 00:46:58,305
Do you remember what I told you?

535
00:46:59,105 --> 00:47:00,585
About someone Tarn liked.

536
00:47:03,065 --> 00:47:04,185
I do.

537
00:47:04,265 --> 00:47:07,464
I would ask permission
to enter Tarn's house

538
00:47:08,025 --> 00:47:10,384
to find clues about this person.

539
00:47:12,825 --> 00:47:14,785
I want to create a miracle.

540
00:47:19,145 --> 00:47:22,225
TO NUT, FROM TOFU

541
00:48:03,265 --> 00:48:04,545
Excuse me, sir.

542
00:48:04,625 --> 00:48:05,505
It's the commander.

543
00:48:08,065 --> 00:48:08,904
Yes.

544
00:48:09,384 --> 00:48:10,665
Roger that.

545
00:49:28,904 --> 00:49:30,384
"Be with you."

546
00:49:30,464 --> 00:49:32,424
BE WITH YOU

547
00:49:32,984 --> 00:49:33,984
What are you doing?

548
00:49:37,984 --> 00:49:39,384
I'm not doing anything.

549
00:49:39,904 --> 00:49:41,345
I'm just arranging your books.

550
00:49:43,625 --> 00:49:44,904
Why this book?

551
00:49:46,065 --> 00:49:47,424
Well?

552
00:49:54,345 --> 00:49:55,185
And this.

553
00:49:56,345 --> 00:49:59,185
You hid the teddy's scarf
in my room, didn't you?

554
00:50:00,345 --> 00:50:01,384
Didn't you?

